song_name: Never Really Been Another Way Out
Never Really Been Another Way Out

version_description: This tab is used best as power chords on an electric guitar.

This is an attempt at laying out all the chords, not all the subtleties of the song. I prefer to play every chord in a bar shape, except for the D chord in the verses. I think the open D sounds better with the pull off note, but both shapes work.
1st tab of this song and my second overall. Hope its relatively accurate.

At the top, I've included the little riff that sounds like it's played on a piano throughout the song and at the end of the song, but also sounds great on guitar. There's also a guitar riff in Em that's played once in a while.
Basic Chords for Wolves At Night by Manchester Orchestra.
All of the tabs have been transposed to not require a capo. All songs are in standard tuning.
